ELI5: Python decorators

You have a gift (your function). You want to wrap it in pretty paper (add logging). Then put it in a box (add authentication). Then tie a bow on it (add caching).

Each layer is a decorator. The gift inside doesn't change. But what the recipient sees is the fully wrapped version.

@bow
@box
@wrapping_paper
def gift():
    return happiness

The decorators apply bottom-up: wrapping_paper first, then box, then bow. The outermost decorator is the first thing the caller "sees."

Just like middleware. request in, response out. The layers are the journey.

